# Generated Artifacts Reading

Do not load huge/generated artifacts wholesale into context. Use source specs, contracts, targeted search, or narrow slices.

## Avoid reading whole files

- `build/**`, `.mojo-cache/**`, `__pycache__/**`
- generated bindings (`*_generated.*`, `gen/**`, vendor stubs)
- large benchmark outputs, profiling dumps, tensor dumps
- full CI artifact archives
- duplicated codegen from `.proto` / schema tools

## Read instead

- hand-written source: `**/*.mojo`, host Python, `.proto`, format docs under `docs/`
- code around the callsite/import/error
- generated files: only the exact symbol/file/range needed for a compile or import error

For large JSON/logs from checks, use targeted `jq` / `rg` / line ranges — never dump entire files into context.
